d mix <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Add remaining 40 g apricots, 40 g cherries and 30 g pistachios and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer mixture into container with ice cream and place into freezer until mixture is firm (approx. 3 hours). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Line a baking tray (20 x 30 cm) with baking paper (ensure tray will fit into freezer). Scoop out ice cream with a spoon and using your hands, shape into approx. 32 bite-sized balls (approx. 25 g). Place onto tray and return to freezer until hard (2-3 hours)."},{"content":"Place dark chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add chilli (optional) and heat <b>4 min\/50°C\/speed 2<b>, until chocolate melts."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Mix <b>until temperature reaches 37°C\/speed 2<b> <strong>,<\/strong> <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>. Transfer into a bowl."},{"content":"Working in batches, remove ice cream balls from freezer. Using two spoons, dip each ball into chocolate, coating them all over, and place back into freezer to set for a minimum of 20 minutes, or until ready to serve (see Tips)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["It is necessary to work quickly to coat ice cream balls in dark chocolate before they melt. Have a couple of trays on rotation in the freezer."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","13h 55m","32 portions"]}